            "id": "4580530",
            "title": "Bed Bath & Beyond soars after earnings as analysts weigh in on the turnaround plan",
            "description": "<html><body><p data-eci=\"true\">Bed Bath &amp; Beyond (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BBBY\" title=\"Bed Bath &amp; Beyond, Inc.\">BBBY</a></span>) soared after issuing its first-quarter earnings report after the closing bell on Monday. The retailer is being sized up by analysts following the earnings update and recent M&amp;A activity.</p>\n<p>Wedbush Securities reiterated an Outperform rating on Bed Bath &amp; Beyond (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BBBY\" title=\"Bed Bath &amp; Beyond, Inc.\">BBBY</a>) after taking in the report. Analyst Alicia Reese noted that the retailer is looking to turbocharge growth and margins by integrating and revitalizing its new home assets into a broader home solutions platform. \"We expect at least $40 million in annualized cost savings and productivity efficiencies within 12–18 months of full integration,\" updated Reese. The firm has an $8.00 price target on BBBY. </p>\n<p>Needham is more cautious with a Hold rating on Bed Bath &amp; Beyond (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BBBY\" title=\"Bed Bath &amp; Beyond, Inc.\">BBBY</a>). Analyst Bernie McTernan said the Q1 highlight for Bed Bath &amp; Beyond (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BBBY\" title=\"Bed Bath &amp; Beyond, Inc.\">BBBY</a>) was revenue growing +6.9% Y/Y (+9.4% ex Canada) to mark the first positive Y/Y revenue growth in over 4 years. \"We are adding Kirkland to our model, which helps revenue, but integration costs are a drag on '26E EBITDA. Our '27 estimates are roughly unchanged. Despite progress achieved by BBBY, we remain on the sidelines as there is still substantial work to be done to reach positive adj. EBITDA and successfully transition the core business from legacy e-commerce to the Everything Home,\" updated McTernan.</p>\n<p>Jefferies also has a Hold rating on Bed Bath &amp; Beyond (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BBBY\" title=\"Bed Bath &amp; Beyond, Inc.\">BBBY</a>). \"Encouragingly, the core business returned to top-line growth while maintaining cost discipline. Management's ambitions for constructing an ecosystem to capture customer spend throughout the journey of homeowners are admirable, given prospects for cross-selling, optimized advertising, and attractive margin profiles of newer service-related businesses,\" updated Jonathan Matuszewski. However, the firm noted that it is early days in the BBBY portfolio approach, which introduces integration risk .</p>\n<p>Shares of BBBY were up 24.9% in premarket action to $6.67, which is the highest trading level in more than three months. Short interest on BBBY is 11.4% of the total float.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
